e configuration file</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--correct\" data-for=\"a\">Right! Skills are loaded via <code>SkillsMiddleware</code> and injected into every prompt. Put the conventions in a <code>.md</code> file in the skills directory.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"b\">The system prompt is fixed. AGENTS.md and skills let you customize per-agent or per-project.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"c\">AGENTS.md is for agent memory (past context), not static instructions. Use skills for conventions.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"d\">Middleware configures which middleware to use, not what content they inject.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n\n<!-- MODULE 7: Sandboxes and MCP -->\n<section class=\"module\" id=\"module-7\">\n  <div class=\"module__inner\">\n\n    <div class=\"module__header animate-in\">\n      <div class=\"module__number\">Module 7</div>\n      <h1 class=\"module__title\">Sandboxes and MCP</h1>\n      <p class=\"module__subtitle\">Run code in remote sandboxes; plug in MCP tool servers.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 1: Local vs Remote -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Local vs. remote execution</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">By default, tools run on <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"Local execution means the AI's tools (file operations, shell commands) run on YOUR machine — your CPU, your filesystem.\">your local machine</span>. With a <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"A sandbox is a remote virtual machine that runs code in a contained environment. Useful for running code that might be dangerous or resource-intensive.\">sandbox</span>, tools run on a remote cloud VM.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout--info\">\n        <span class=\"callout__icon\">🏨</span>\n        <div class=\"callout__content\">\n          <div class=\"callout__title\">The hotel desk metaphor</div>\n          Local execution: you're at your own desk, you can do anything yourself. Remote sandbox: you're at a hotel front desk — you ask the concierge to do things for you, and they do it in the back.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"icon-row\">\n        <div class=\"icon-item\">\n          <span class=\"icon-item__emoji\">💻</span>\n          <span class=\"icon-item__label\">Local — your machine</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"icon-item\">\n          <span class=\"icon-item__emoji\">☁️</span>\n          <span class=\"icon-item__label\">Sandbox — cloud VM</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">🌊</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">Modal</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Serverless compute from Cohere.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">🚀</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">Daytona</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Managed dev environments.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">🔄</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">Runloop</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Remote execution platform.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">📊</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">LangSmith</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Tracing and evaluation.</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 2: Backend Interface Abstraction -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Backend interface abstraction</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">The same tool calls route to different <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"A backend is the underlying system that actually executes file operations and shell commands. LocalBackend runs on your machine; SandboxBackend runs on a remote VM.\">backends</span> depending on the sandbox setting.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"data-flow\">\n        <div class=\"data-flow__track\" style=\"justify-content: center; gap: 16px;\">\n          <div class=\"flow-actor\">\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-1);\">🤖</div>\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__name\">Agent</div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flow-arrow\" style=\"position:relative;flex:none;width:40px;\"></div>\n          <div class=\"flow-actor\">\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-3);\">🔀</div>\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__name\">Router</div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flow-arrow\" style=\"position:relative;flex:none;width:40px;\"></div>\n          <div class=\"flow-actor\">\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-5);\">💻</div>\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__name\">LocalBackend</div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flow-arrow\" style=\"position:relative;flex:none;width:40px; opacity: 0.3;\"></div>\n          <div class=\"flow-actor\" style=\"opacity: 0.5;\">\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-4);\">☁️</div>\n            <div class=\"flow-actor__name\">SandboxBackend</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">Backend selection (from agent.py)</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<div class=\"code-pre\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>if sandbox is None:</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>    # LOCAL MODE</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span>    backend = LocalShellBackend(root_dir=root_dir)</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>else:</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    # REMOTE SANDBOX MODE</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>    backend = sandbox</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 1-3</strong> — No sandbox: use <code>LocalShellBackend</code> for local file/shell operations.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 4-6</strong> — With sandbox: use the provided sandbox backend (Modal, Daytona, etc.).</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 3: Sandbox Detection -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Sandbox detection</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">The CLI detects the sandbox type from the <code>--sandbox</code> flag and creates the appropriate backend.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"step-cards\">\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">1</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Parse --sandbox flag</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\"><code>--sandbox modal</code> or <code>--sandbox daytona</code></div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">2</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Create backend</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">Factory creates the appropriate sandbox client.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">3</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Inject into agent</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">Sandbox backend replaces local backend in the graph.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout--accent\">\n        <span class=\"callout__icon\">🔌</span>\n        <div class=\"callout__content\">\n          <div class=\"callout__title\">Same API, different execution</div>\n          The agent calls <code>execute(\"ls\")</code> — it doesn't know if it's running locally or remotely. The backend abstraction makes this transparent.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 4: MCP Integration -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">MCP integration</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\"><span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"MCP = Model Context Protocol. It's like USB for AI — a standard way to connect AI models to external tools and data sources.\">MCP</span> (Model Context Protocol) connects your AI to external tools via a standardized interface.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout--info\">\n        <span class=\"callout__icon\">🔌</span>\n        <div class=\"callout__content\">\n          <div class=\"callout__title\">MCP = USB for AI</div>\n          Just as USB lets you plug many devices into one port, MCP lets you connect many tool servers to one AI. The AI sees them all as available tools.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"step-cards\">\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">1</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Discover mcp.json</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">MCP config files declare available servers.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">2</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Spawn server processes</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">CLI starts each tool server as a subprocess.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">3</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Connect tools</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">Tools from MCP servers added to agent's tool list.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"file-tree\">\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__name\">mcp.json</span> — MCP server config</div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">{</span></span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">  \"mcpServers\": {</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">    \"filesystem\": {</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">      \"command\": \"npx\",</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">      \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\"]</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">    }</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">  }</span></div>\n        <div class=\"file-tree__line\"><span class=\"file-tree__indent\">}</span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 5: Quiz -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Check your understanding</h2>\n\n      <div class=\"quiz\" id=\"quiz-module-7\">\n        <div class=\"quiz__question\">You want to add a new sandbox provider. What's the minimum you need to change?</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__options\">\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"a\">Rewrite the entire agent.py</button>\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"b\">Update command_registry.py</button>\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"c\" data-correct=\"true\">Add a new backend class and update the factory</button>\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"d\">Modify every tool function</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--correct\" data-for=\"c\">Right! The backend abstraction means you add a new backend class (conforming to the protocol) and register it in the factory. The agent code doesn't need changes.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"a\">The whole point of the abstraction is avoiding that. You only add a new backend.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"b\">command_registry.py handles slash commands, not sandbox backends.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"d\">Tools call the backend interface, they don't know about the implementation.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n\n<!-- MODULE 8: Making It Feel Real -->\n<section class=\"module module--warm\" id=\"module-8\">\n  <div class=\"module__inner\">\n\n    <div class=\"module__header animate-in\">\n      <div class=\"module__number\">Module 8</div>\n      <h1 class=\"module__title\">Making It Feel Real</h1>\n      <p class=\"module__subtitle\">Slash commands, pretty output, polish.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 1: Slash Command Registry -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Slash command registry</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">All <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"Slash commands are special commands that start with /, like /clear, /help, /model. They provide quick access to features without typing full sentences.\">slash commands</span> are defined as <code>SlashCommand</code> entries in one place.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">SlashCommand dataclass (from command_registry.py)</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<div class=\"code-pre\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>class SlashCommand:</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span>    name: str           # e.g. \"/clear\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>    description: str   # shown in autocomplete</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    bypass_tier: BypassTier  # queue priority</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>    hidden_keywords: str = \"\"  # fuzzy match</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">7</span><span>    aliases: tuple[str, ...] = ()</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 1</strong> — <code>frozen=True</code> makes it immutable. <code>slots=True</code> optimizes memory.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 3</strong> — <code>name</code>: the command string users type.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 4</strong> — <code>description</code>: shown in autocomplete dropdown.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 5</strong> — <code>bypass_tier</code>: controls when the command can run (see below).</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 6</strong> — <code>hidden_keywords</code>: terms that also trigger this command in fuzzy search.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">🚪</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">ALWAYS</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Run regardless of busy state (/quit)</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">⚡</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">IMMEDIATE_UI</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Open modal immediately (/model)</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">📤</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">SIDE_EFFECT_FREE</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Run now, defer output (/mcp)</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__icon\">⏳</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__title\">QUEUED</div>\n          <div class=\"pattern-card__desc\">Wait for idle (/clear, /help)</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 2: Build /clear /model /help -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Build /clear, /model, /help</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">Each slash command has a handler in the app that routes to the right function.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">SlashCommand entries (from command_registry.py)</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<div class=\"code-pre\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>SlashCommand(</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>    name=\"/clear\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span>    description=\"Clear chat and start new thread\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>    bypass_tier=BypassTier.QUEUED,</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    hidden_keywords=\"reset\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>),</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">7</span><span>SlashCommand(</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">8</span><span>    name=\"/model\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">9</span><span>    description=\"Switch or configure model\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">10</span><span>    bypass_tier=BypassTier.IMMEDIATE_UI,</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">11</span><span>),</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">12</span><span>SlashCommand(</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">13</span><span>    name=\"/help\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">14</span><span>    description=\"Show help\",</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">15</span><span>    bypass_tier=BypassTier.QUEUED,</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">16</span><span>),</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>/clear</strong> — Clears message history. QUEUED so it waits for the AI to finish.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>/model</strong> — Opens model selection UI. IMMEDIATE_UI so it doesn't wait.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>/help</strong> — Shows help. QUEUED to avoid interrupting active work.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"group-chat\">\n        <div class=\"group-chat__header\">\n          <span>⌨️</span>\n          <span>Slash command routing</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"group-chat__body\">\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">You</div>\n            /model gpt-4o\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--center\">\n            Detected slash command: /model\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--right\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">CLI</div>\n            Switching to gpt-4o...\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 3: Textual TUI Basics -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Textual TUI basics</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\"><span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"Textual is a Python TUI framework built by the same people who made Rich. It provides reactive widgets, async support, and CSS styling for terminals.\">Textual</span> builds the interactive terminal UI with widgets, async events, and CSS styling.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout--info\">\n        <span class=\"callout__icon\">🎨</span>\n        <div class=\"callout__content\">\n          <div class=\"callout__title\">Why Textual?</div>\n          Textual is async-native (perfect for streaming AI responses), reactive (widgets update automatically), and uses CSS for styling (familiar to web developers).\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">Minimal Textual app (adapted from app.py)</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<div class=\"code-pre\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>from textual.app import App, ComposeResult</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>from textual.widgets import Static, Input</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span></span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>class MyApp(App):</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>        yield Static(\"Deep Agents CLI\", id=\"header\")</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">7</span><span>        yield Input(placeholder=\"Type a message...\")</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">8</span><span></span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">9</span><span>    async def on_input_submitted(self, event):</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">10</span><span>        await self.agent.run(event.value)</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 5-7</strong> — <code>compose()</code> declares the widget tree: a header and an input.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 9-10</strong> — <code>on_input_submitted</code> is an event handler. When user presses Enter, it sends the message to the agent.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 4: Glyph Auto-Detection -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Glyph auto-detection</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">The CLI detects whether your terminal supports <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"Unicode glyphs are special characters like ⏺, ✓, ✗ that look better than ASCII alternatives like (*), [OK], [X].\">Unicode glyphs</span> and falls back to ASCII if needed.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">Glyph detection (from config.py)</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<div class=\"code-pre\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>def _detect_charset_mode() -> CharsetMode:</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>    env_mode = os.environ.get(\"UI_CHARSET_MODE\", \"auto\")</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span>    if env_mode == \"unicode\":</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>        return CharsetMode.UNICODE</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    if env_mode == \"ascii\":</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>        return CharsetMode.ASCII</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">7</span><span>    # Auto: check stdout encoding and LANG</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">8</span><span>    encoding = getattr(sys.stdout, \"encoding\", \"\") or \"\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">9</span><span>    if \"utf\" in encoding.lower():</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">10</span><span>        return CharsetMode.UNICODE</span></span>\n<span class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">11</span><span>    return CharsetMode.ASCII</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 2</strong> — Check <code>UI_CHARSET_MODE</code> env var first for explicit override.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 8-10</strong> — Check stdout encoding. If it contains \"utf\", use Unicode glyp